Libatom release NEWS
====================

2013-04-09 libatom 0.2.4
------------------------
This release is an official release in the 0.2 stable series.

New Features:

* add operators ==, !=, ostream<< for blob
* pretty print blobs
* add factory for empty blob
* add typedefs for int and float

Bug fixes:

* use unsigned char for blob bytes


2013-02-13 libatom 0.2.2
------------------------
This release is an official release in the 0.2 stable series.

New Features:

* Add Blob and BlobValue
* More doc about supported value types


2012-12-28 libatom 0.2.0
------------------------
This release is an official release in the 0.2 stable series.

New Features:

* IntValue and FloatValue now have the setMin, getMin, setMax and getMax methods.
* Check that float/int is within range when setting it.
* Add conversion from message to lo_message
* Add toInt(), toFloat(), toString(), Value::isType()
* Support va_list arguments
* Add automatic conversion of floatvalue to int, and intvalue to float

Bug fixes:

* Put VERSION constant in the atom namespace
* Actually run the tests
* Various corrections in StringValue
* Change from long int to long long


2012-10-17 libatom 0.1.4
------------------------
This release is a developer snapshot in the 0.1 unstable series. 

New Features:

* add PointerValue and DictValue


2012-10-17 libatom 0.1.2
------------------------
This release is a developer snapshot in the 0.1 unstable series. 

New Features:

* Add IntValue, StringValue, BooleanValue, FloatValue, NullValue, ListValue
* Remove Atom


2012-09-28 libatom 0.1.0
------------------------
This release is a developer snapshot in the 0.1 unstable series. 

It is the initial release of libatom.

New Features:

* Provide a generic container for simple data types.

